Even offline, there is no guarantee that a research participant is completely honest.
On Facebook, it's impossible to know how much of what's on a user profile and in posts is true.
"What you say on Facebook and what you do off Facebook are two completely different things", says Selwyn.
So despite his years as a technology researcher, Selwyn thinks that a clipboard and a pen are still the best research tools anyone can use.
