The participation of political representatives of different political tendencies in election campaigns testified to the impartiality of Trinijove's work.
In addition to the President of the Generalitat (Parliament of the Autonomous Region of Catalonia), Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol, the celebrations were attended by the former Socialist Minister of Education Ernest Maragall and the former mayor and then left-green city councillor Ricard Goma.
The large hall of Fabra i Coats was also visited by the current Catalan Minister of Social Affairs and Family Affairs, Josep Lluís Cleries, and the Director General of Social Work at Sparkasse La Caixa, Jaume Lanaspa.
Mas stressed that Trinijove was created in very difficult times and that the times are no less complicated today, but added that the work done so far "is a good foundation".
For the President of the Generalitat, Trinijove is a role model who knows how to fight against difficult circumstances and gives hope to people in difficulty.
"The economic crisis is nothing new for the club and the work it does", he said.
Occupied house where huge parties were held has been cleared
The owners occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the building at 51 Balmes Street, Barcelona.
The 12 squatters left the building yesterday afternoon without resisting.
It seems that the nightmares of the neighbours of the house at 51 Balmes Street have come to an end.
Twelve people left voluntarily yesterday at noon the building they had illegally occupied and where they had organized huge parties that had driven the neighbourhood to despair, the eviction was carried out by judicial order without any police intervention.
After the evacuation, the door lock was replaced to avoid a similar situation.
"From now on, access will be controlled", confirmed the building manager.
The squatters who occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the building - the rest were inhabited - took the entire electrical system and part of the water supply, painted the walls and left all kinds of trash, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
The three lower floors were used for huge parties that lasted up to two days and drove the tenants to despair.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which also suffered damage.
